HEADWORD: Surmark
<hw>Sur"mark`</hw> <pr>(s⟦ucir⟧r"m⟦aum⟧rk`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Shipbuilding)</fld> <def>A mark made on the molds of a ship, when
building, to show where the angles of the timbers are to be
placed.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>sirmark</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Surmisable</ent>⟦br⟧
